title: Wintershall drills dry well in the North Sea
text:
Tip : Use comma (,) to separate multiple quotes. Learn more... 
Wed, Jul 15, 2015, 10:08 BST - UK Markets close in 6 hrs 22 mins Wintershall drills dry well in the North Sea Reuters - UK Focus – 2 hours 32 minutes ago 136.50 -1.50 
OSLO, July 15 (Reuters) - Wintershall, German BASF's oil and gas subsidiary, drilled a dry well in the Norwegian sector of the North Sea, southeast of the Yme field, the Norwegian Petroleum Directorate said on Thursday. 
Wintershall, operator of the field, has a 40 percent stake, while other partners include Centrica Resources and Lundin with a 30 percent stake each.
